betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Welcome to your new home, it may be small now, but soon, you will have a thriving island for you and your friends (if you want to share it). You might be looking around you and wondering where you are and what is the Aether, just follow these quests and you will be on your way to automation in no time.

It may not look like there's very much here, but you will be surprised. Cut down the one tree you have and make a crafting table.

You will be given a reward for this quest, be careful this food can rotten. Eat it fast and enjoy.

The Sieve is (as the name indicates) used to sieve small particles from less consistent blocks, such as Sand or Gravel. The blocks to sieve are applied by right-clicking on the sieve holding them. After that, the sieve has to be right-clicked until the item is fully sieved. Then the items sieves out of the block drop from the sieve.

Tip: You can put 2 or more sieve together and they will work like one.

WARNING: The block used to sieve the items will be completely lost then!

You can start by creating a Skyroot Crook which will give you extra chances of dropping more sapling.

Once you get yourself some wood, you can start expanding your island and build yourself a crafting table and some chests to store your new stuff.

But don't wait for saplings to grow into trees. Instead, twerk around the saplings to apply bone meal effect.

(*Tip: You can get bonemeal by sifting dust in a string mesh).
This Stone Hammer variant is crafted from Holystone and Holystone Sticks.

You might have noticed by now that the only dirt available to you is Aether Dirt, you're probably going to need regular dirt before you can grow food. You can make some wooden barrels from some skyroot planks, which you should have plenty of by now. These barrels can be used to make dirt when organic matter like leaves and saplings are added.

If you pour Vanilla Seeds and Leaves it will make Vanilla Dirt.

If you pour Skyroot Leaves and Sapling it will make Aether Dirt.

Siefting Aether Dirt into a String Mesh will provide with Stone Pebbles, where combined, become Cobblestones. When using a Combined Hammer on the cobblestones, many variant of pebbles will drop, including the HolyStone ones, where combined, will become the Holystones.
Crushed Granite comes from using a compressed hammer on Granite, and brings you closer to obtaining Red Sand.
Wooden crooks have a low durability, but this can helped by crafting 9 crooks together for a Compressed Crook.
Seeds are dropped from sifting Aether Dirt in a String Mesh.
Gravel can be obtained from Crushed Skystone. (By breaking it with a Hammer).
Before you can get sieving for seeds, your sieve is going to need a mesh, and for that, you need string. Craft a crook and use it to break skyroot leaves, and some leaves will eventually drop string.

§
You can make water by pouring sapling into an Oak Crucible.

Ressources are scarce, and grinding can take time. A mob farm could help bring variety and offer a way to accelerate things.

Create a small room, about 25 blocks away from your main island, and ensure it is dark. Craft a sword, then hunt down some monsters until you have some loots.
Dust can be used to obtain Clay and many gem ressources.
Sand be used to plant Cacti and Sugar Canes, as well as be turned into glass. It can also be sieved for cacao beans and prismarine shards.
To move to the metals age, you will need to sift Gravel in a Flint Mesh or better.
A Flint Stiffened Mesh will allow you to sieve Aether Dirt, Gravel, Sand, Dust and other blocks, but provide different rewards than the String one.
In order to obtain hot fluids, you will need a fireproof Container. Crucibles are used to melt stones into lava.
Claw buckets can be used to move lava only once, but it's an early alternative until you can obtain an iron one.

To get started on the Metals age, you going to need a Compressed Hammer of any kind.

Use the Compressed Hammer to Break Holystone to transform it into Crushed Skystone.

Or Break Cobblestone with it to get Stone Pebbles of all Stone variants.
Crushed Andasite comes from using a compressed hammer on Andasite, and brings you closer to obtaining Sand.
To sieve dirt, you're going to need a string mesh. You should have plenty of string by now, with your crooks.
The Transmutation Table functions as a battery for EMC energy, a charger for EMC storage items, as a library of blueprints and as a fabricator of items.
Use a Compressed Hammer on Oak Logs to obtain Wood Chippings.
Crushed Diorite comes from using a compressed hammer on Diorite, and brings you closer to obtaining Dust.
To start you alchemical journey, you will some components, which the Convalence Dust are used for. Beginners starts with the most basic ones.

Get yourself a skyroot pickaxe out of the skyroot wood you just got.
Make sure to set the vein-mine key (Ore Excavator) from the controls setting then veinmine the Aether Dirt and mine the Holystone under it. Get yourself at least 9 of each block under your island.
This Alchemist tool is used to find EMC values of blocks.
Now that you have a Sieve, start by sifting Aether Dirt to get Oak Seeds.
Now that you have obtained clay, use it to make a clay bucket and use the Clay Bucket to get water out of the Oak Crucible.
Another component used in your alchemist journey.
To be able to get the water you just made out of the crucible, you going to need a bucket. Buckets can be made out of clay. To get clay right click an Oak Crucible with a block of Dust.
From the pebbles dropped from cobblestone, now go and craft Granite Blocks with them.
From the pebbles dropped from cobblestone, now go and craft Diorite Blocks with them.
From the pebbles dropped from cobblestone, now go and craft Andesite Blocks with them.
You can get vanilla sapling from sifting Aether Dirt in a String Mesh.
Now that you have access to Vanilla trees, get your self some semi-auto making of Dirt.
Another component used in your alchemist journey.

The Alchemical Chest is a large chest, capable of holding 104 stacks of items (compared to a vanilla double-chest's 72 stacks). In addition, the chest can be upgraded with some utility items that perform special effects.

It is also used as a crafting component in the creation of other powerful tools.
An Alchemical Chest on the go!
Similar to the Crafting Table on a Stick, this is a Transmutation Table on the go!
This tool will help repair your tools, which can not be repaired normally.
Your journey as an alchemist will bring you to develop better source fuels than Coal and Charcoal. This is the first step to a better alchemy fuel: it burns four times as long as regular Coal.
This next step will double the burn time of its predecesor. Legends says it can be used to bring stars to you.
This third evolution in Fuel extends the burn time by a factor of four.
This discovery can be lead to an Alchemy Revolution. Will you use it for tools, weapons or protection?
Who would have though it possible? Another coloured matter, and with more potency than the dark one? What can this lead too?
Klein Stars are EMC storage item, and can hold up EMC.
For each tier improvement, the EMC capacity increases by a factor of 4.
For each tier improvement, the EMC capacity increases by a factor of 4.
For each tier improvement, the EMC capacity increases by a factor of 4.
This was though to be the final step in Klein Stars, but rumors talk of a fabled alchemist whom went even further...
Legends were true, and a more powerful Klein Star can be obtained.
Protection? This new set will put the Diamond Armorset to shame.
This matter also offers more protection than its dark counter part. It's time to test it.

Who knows what this new Klein Star can make? This new Storage Capacity could potential be used with great effect with Red Matter, but how can be combine them? Maybe we will need to revisit all our progression as an Alchemist, and see what can be used from our previous tools?

An advanved Axe that used energy as durability.

It also has an AOE mode.
Obtaining food will be critical if you are going to survive on your island.
This version can scan further than its predecesor.
This superior tool can give the highest value block and a sum of blocks in its range.
Tools and Weapons? This new tools will allow you to work faster (or kill monsters faster) than ever!
It's time to test this new matter on our toys.
The properties of this matter even allows to condense our improved toys into more portable versions.
This is an essential component to the famous EMC Factory or Energy Flower. It should be placed orthogonally-adjacent to any Anti-Matter Relay.
A better version of the Energy Collector.
The best version of the Energy Collector.
This is the core of the Energy Factory or EMC Flower. It also acts like the previous Condensers, where you can transmute items with EMC into another item.
The Energy Condenser MK2 is an upgraded version of the Energy Condenser. In addition to being substantially faster than the Energy Condenser, the MK2 also has a separate inventory for output.
This is an essential component to the famous EMC Factory or Energy Flower. It should be placed orthogonally-adjacent to the Alchemical chest.
A better version of the Anti-Matter Relay.
The best version of the Anti-Matter Relay.

Jump down from your island and go look for bigger islands in which you can find Crystals you can use for magic.

Tip: You can get back to your island with the command "/island home"

§UAnd use this reward to get the sleep in bed research to get started with Thaumcraft.
You can get worms to speed up string production and also they are useful as food source.
Bone Crook is another alternative to the skyroot and wooden crooks, with a slightly better durability than the compressed wooden crook, but using bones instead of wood.
Sift Dust in a String Mesh to get Bone Meal.
Basic crafting material used for crafting machines and other stuff.
Sift Sand in a String Mesh to get Cocoa Beans.
You might have noticed by now that you can get Grains of Infinity from sifting Dust Blocks, get some to get started with Ender IO.

Holystone tools are for what Vanilla Stone tools are for. Not only do they have increase durability, but they also are the next tier to break blocks and mine faster.

Start by sieve some Aether dirt in a string mesh to obtain seeds, and compost them into Vanilla Dirt, so you can start a Farm.

Sift Dust in an Iron Mesh to obtain these drops.
Sift Sand in a Diamond Mesh to get Prismarine Shards.
Obtained Crushed Stones are a neccessary steps towards obtaining Gravel, Sand and Dust. Using your Compressed Hammer on Holystone will give you Crushed Sky Stone.
Now that you can obtain's overworld dirt and wood, it's time to get cobblestone to officially go to the Stone Age.
Using your newly Compressed Hammer on Cobblestone will provide you with Pebbles from Andasite, Diorite and Granite.

Welcome to Skylands, a misterious place found in The Aether. For now you might only be in a small island but as you progress through the modpack you will explore many more bigger islands. it may be small now, but soon, you will have a thriving island for you and your friends (if you want to share it). You might be looking around you and wondering where you are and what is the Aether, just follow these quests and you will be on your way to automation and exploration in no time.
Discover powerful alchemical tools, items, and devices. Break down unwanted items into EMC (Energy-Matter Covalence) and use that EMC to create new items.
